This version handles the fact that `getCurrentOperations()` can return `null` by capturing the return value as an `Optional`.  The `Optional`&#39;s stream will be empty when `getCurrentOperations()` returns `null`, and `anyMatch()` returns `false` on an empty stream.

The `map()` of the inner stream could be omitted in favor of a more complex predicate for its `anyMatch()`, but I think the version with `map()` is clearer.

